Class BinaryPQ<E>

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<E>, PQueue<E>
public class BinaryPQ<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PQueue<E>

An array backed binary heap priority queue.

This class adapts a binary heap to the PQueue interface. As such, it supports requeueing of objects by using cells.

This class is similar to the java PriorityQueue, however the implementation maintains the cells for objects in the queue along with the objects themselves. Consequently, if re-queueing is not required, then we recomend using the PriorityQueue interface.

requeue

public void requeue(Cell<E> cell)
Requeue an element in the queue. If the priority for the element has changed since it was last requeued (or inserted), this operation will adjust the priority queue according to the new priority.

This priority queue is not monotonic: it supports increases as well as decreases in priority.

Specified by:
requeue in interface PQueue<E>
Parameters:
